'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">In view of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">rather</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> abstract nature of the litigation and the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> politicized environment</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> in which it often operates, it </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is doubtful whether a system of pre-enactment review</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> would </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">take root easily in the United Kingdom</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">1 November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">See instance, </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">the US Supreme Court with Marbury </span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt">v. Madison, 5 US 137 and</span><span style="font-family:Verdana; font-size:12pt"> the French Constitutional Council